I understand that failure to abide by the regulations may warrant a suspension from usage of the venue and/or further punitive action where applicable, according to the SOP above.

Priority System (For Ad Hoc Bookings)
1. Any CSC committee, House committee and CAPT Support (can book 3 weeks in advance)
2. Any CSC-affiliated committee (can book 2 weeks in advance)
3. House cell groups (e.g. Christian cell groups) and other groups not mentioned above (can book 1 week in advance)

This Booking Form must be submitted at least 5 working days in advance of your booking day. If not, your booking may not be processed.
Bookings that are made beyond the stipulated time stated above in the Priority System will not be processed.

Committees are strongly encouraged to use SR3-6 if their group size is less than 20 pax. This is so that bigger committees can use the combined SR 1 and 2 which can hold more people.

Please refrain from making bookings during recess week, reading week and examination week as the SRs will be used for academic activities.
